KW  - Private investment
KW  - Public capital
KW  - Infrastructure
AB  - Despite recent successes in stabilization and structural reforms in many developing countries, the private investment response to date has been mixed, even among the strongest reformers. This disappointing result can be partly explained by the continued poor provision of public capital and services. We test this hypothesis using unique firm-level data on investment and provision of public infrastructure services. The results suggest that poor complementary public capital significantly reduces private investment. However, firms can substitute for deficient public services by investing in complementary capital themselves. But this comes at a cost: less productive capital will be installed.
