KW  - Hard budget
AB  - Governments and aid agencies target transfers to the poor, but audits to deter the rich are costly. This paper analyzes how community information can improve targeting. If each community is given a hard budget constraint, then targeting costs can be substantially reduced by asking recipients to make reports about each other. Audits are threatened in the event of a disagreement but never carried out in equilibrium. This scheme is immune to collusion.
